President Uhuru Kenyatta on Sunday left the country for Seychelles on a three-day State Visit to the Indian Ocean Island nation. The president was received at Seychelles International Airport on Mahe Island by his Sychellois host Wavel Ramkalawan at the start of his visit. President Kenyatta, who is leading a Kenyan Government delegation on the visit, was accorded an elaborate state reception. The reception included a Guard of Honour mounted by the country's military, Seychelles People's Defence Force, and a 21-Gun Salute.